e:T829,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Codepliant generate a privacy policy?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant scans your codebase for data collection patterns: cookies, analytics SDKs (Google Analytics, Mixpanel, Segment), authentication providers, ORMs (Prisma, Drizzle, Mongoose, TypeORM, Sequelize), and API integrations. It then generates a legally-informed privacy policy that accurately reflects what your application actually does."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this better than online privacy policy generators?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Traditional generators ask you to fill out questionnaires and hope you know every data practice in your app. Codepliant reads your source code directly, achieving 97.8% detection precision across 100 real-world GitHub repositories. It catches things you might forget to mention."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What data practices does Codepliant detect?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant detects cookies, local storage, session management, authentication (OAuth, JWT, SSO), database schemas and ORMs, analytics and tracking, payment processing, email collection, file uploads, geolocation, device fingerprinting, AI/ML model usage, third-party API calls, and more."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the generated privacy policy GDPR compliant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant generates privacy policies that include GDPR-required sections: data controller information, legal basis for processing, data subject rights, data retention, international transfers, and cookie disclosures. However, we recommend having a lawyer review the final document for your specific jurisdiction."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does it cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The CLI is free and open source. You can generate privacy policies in Markdown at no cost. Pro ($29/mo) adds HTML, PDF output, and custom branding. Team ($79/mo) adds monorepo support and a compliance API."}}]}b:["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"SoftwareApplication\",\"name\":\"Codepliant Privacy Policy Generator\",\"applicationCategory\":\"DeveloperApplication\",\"operatingSystem\":\"macOS, Linux, Windows\",\"description\":\"Free privacy policy generator that scans your codebase to create accurate, comprehensive privacy policies.\",\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"Offer\",\"price\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"USD\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"py-20 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[680px] mx-auto","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-accent mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase","children":"Free Tool"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"Free Privacy Policy Generator for Developers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-muted mb-12","children":"Most privacy policy generators ask you to fill out a questionnaire. Codepliant reads your code instead. It scans your codebase for cookies, analytics, databases, auth providers, and API integrations, then generates a privacy policy that accurately reflects your application."}],"$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14"]}]}]],null,"$L15"]}]
